    "body": "# üêû bug report\r\n### Affected package\r\n@angular/core\r\n### Description\r\nWhen i try to extends built-in Angular decorator ```Component```, application was crashed with error: ```Failed to load my.component.html (404 Not Found)```.\r\n\r\nHere is my code of decorator:\r\n```\r\nexport function MyComponent(cfg: Component): TypeDecorator {\r\n  const decorator = Component(cfg);\r\n  return function (cls: Type<any>) {\r\n    return decorator(cls);\r\n  };\r\n}\r\n```\r\nHere's its usage:\r\n```\r\n@MyComponent({\r\n  selector: 'app-my-component',\r\n  templateUrl: './my.component.html',\r\n  styleUrls: ['./my.component.scss'],\r\n})\r\nexport class MyComponent {\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI found out that if you use the standard ```Component``` decorator, then meta.templateUrl will resolve in meta.template. But if i use custom directive, nothing happend. Application trying to get ```my.component.html``` from ```http://localhost/my.component.html``` by xhr request, and crashed when receive error 404.\r\n\r\nWhy this happens I do not understand, most likely it is a bug.\r\n\r\nHere is my dependencies: \r\n```        \"@angular/animations\": \"^7.2.7\",\r\n        \"@angular/common\": \"^7.2.7\",\r\n        \"@angular/compiler\": \"^7.2.7\",\r\n        \"@angular/core\": \"^7.2.7\",\r\n        \"@angular/forms\": \"^7.2.7\",\r\n        \"@angular/http\": \"^7.2.7\",\r\n        \"@angular/platform-browser\": \"^7.2.7\",\r\n        \"@angular/platform-browser-dynamic\": \"^7.2.7\",\r\n        \"@angular/router\": \"^7.2.7\",```"
