    "body": "# üêû bug report\r\n\r\n### Affected Package\r\n`@angular/bazel`\r\n\r\n\r\n### Is this a regression?\r\nno clue\r\n\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nIf a typical developer in his existing CLI project never mentioned option `angularCompilerOptions.fullTemplateTypeCheck` before and try to (ng-add) bazel in his project. \r\nThen run `ng serve` or `ng serve --prod` he will get **hundreds** or errors in his console and serving will fail due tue templates mistakes! \r\n\r\n**This candisrupt users and discourage  them to try bazel!!!**\r\n\r\n## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction\r\nFor repro you can clone [this existing CLI project](https://github.com/istiti/bazel-FullTemplateTypeCheck) that I ng-add bazel to it and make intentionally this error in [app.component.html](https://github.com/istiti/bazel-FullTemplateTypeCheck/blob/master/src/app/app.component.html#L5-L10) template\r\n\r\nTo get error : `npm install && ng s`\r\n\r\n## üî• Error\r\nAll errors that `fullTemplateTypeCheck` can throw and fail to compile. Here I produce this error: \r\n<pre><code>\r\n/home/.../src/BUILD.bazel:15:1: Compiling Angular templates (ngc) //src:src failed (Exit 1)\r\n.../app.component.html(10,7): : Property 'propNotExist' does not exist on type 'AppComponent'\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n## üåç  Your Environment\r\n\r\n**Angular Version:**\r\n<pre><code>\r\nAngular CLI: 8.0.0-rc.4\r\nNode: 10.15.3\r\nOS: linux x64\r\nAngular: 8.0.0-rc.4\r\n... animations, bazel, cli, common, compiler, compiler-cli, core\r\n... forms, language-service, platform-browser\r\n... platform-browser-dynamic, router\r\n\r\nPackage                           Version\r\n-----------------------------------------------------------\r\n@angular-devkit/architect         0.800.0-rc.4\r\n@angular-devkit/build-angular     0.800.0-rc.4\r\n@angular-devkit/build-optimizer   0.800.0-rc.4\r\n@angular-devkit/build-webpack     0.800.0-rc.4\r\n@angular-devkit/core              8.0.0-rc.4\r\n@angular-devkit/schematics        8.0.0-rc.4\r\n@bazel/bazel                      0.25.1\r\n@bazel/ibazel                     0.10.3\r\n@bazel/karma                      0.27.12\r\n@bazel/typescript                 0.27.12\r\n@ngtools/webpack                  8.0.0-rc.4\r\n@schematics/angular               8.0.0-rc.4\r\n@schematics/update                0.800.0-rc.4\r\nrxjs                              6.4.0\r\ntypescript                        3.4.5\r\nwebpack                           4.30.0\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n**Anything else relevant?**\r\nBazel always consider `fullTemplateTypeCheck` as enabled. It is important to note: even if we set to **FALSE** `angularCompilerOptions.fullTemplateTypeCheck` in `tsconfig.json` it is enabled.\r\n\r\nI think by default `fullTemplateTypeCheck` should be disabled like in CLI without bazel and let users enable it intentionally inside `tsconfig.json`\r\n\r\ncc @kyliau "
