    "body": "<!--üîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖ\r\n\r\nOh hi there! üòÑ\r\n\r\nTo expedite issue processing please search open and closed issues before submitting a new one.\r\nExisting issues often contain information about workarounds, resolution, or progress updates.\r\n\r\nüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖ-->\r\n\r\n\r\n# üêû bug report\r\n\r\n### Affected Package\r\n<!-- Can you pin-point one or more @angular/* packages as the source of the bug? -->\r\n<!-- ‚úçÔ∏èedit: --> The issue is caused by package  \r\n@angular/router\r\n\r\n### Is this a regression?\r\nNot sure\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n<!-- ‚úçÔ∏è-->  \r\n\r\nI have a lazy-loaded module in an angular app. I am adding it dynamically to the route using <pre>     this.router.config.unshift( this.theOletObj );</pre>\r\nIt errors out and the module and its component doesn't get dynamically loaded  : \r\n\r\n## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction \r\nhttps://stackblitz.com/edit/angular-raaom9 \r\n<!-- ‚úçÔ∏è--> https://stackblitz.com/...\r\n\r\n<!--\r\nIf StackBlitz is not suitable for reproduction of your issue, please create a minimal GitHub repository with the reproduction of the issue.\r\nA good way to make a minimal reproduction is to create a new app via `ng new repro-app` and add the minimum possible code to show the problem. \r\nShare the link to the repo below along with step-by-step instructions to reproduce the problem, as well as expected and actual behavior.\r\n\r\nIssues that don't have enough info and can't be reproduced will be closed.\r\n\r\nYou can read more about issue submission guidelines here: https://github.com/angular/angular/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#-submitting-an-issue\r\n-->\r\n\r\n## üî• Exception or Error\r\n<pre><code> preview-4adb70f742b91f09679fb.js:1 ERROR Error: Uncaught (in promise): Error: Cannot find 'BaseModule' in './modules/base/base.module'\r\nError: Cannot find 'BaseModule' in './modules/base/base.module'\r\n    at checkNotEmpty (system_js_ng_module_factory_loader.ts:91)\r\n    at eval (system_js_ng_module_factory_loader.ts:71)\r\n    at ZoneDelegate.invoke (zone.js:391)\r\n    at Object.onInvoke (ng_zone.ts:273)\r\n    at ZoneDelegate.invoke (zone.js:390)\r\n    at Zone.run (zone.js:150)\r\n    at eval (zone.js:889)\r\n    at ZoneDelegate.invokeTask (zone.js:423)\r\n\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n\r\n## üåç  Your Environment\r\n\r\n**Angular Version:**\r\n<pre><code> \r\nAngular CLI: 7.3.9\r\nNode: 10.15.3\r\nOS: linux x64\r\nAngular: 7.2.15\r\n... animations, common, compiler, compiler-cli, core, forms\r\n... language-service, platform-browser, platform-browser-dynamic\r\n... router\r\n\r\nPackage                            Version\r\n------------------------------------------------------------\r\n@angular-devkit/architect          0.13.9\r\n@angular-devkit/build-angular      0.13.9\r\n@angular-devkit/build-optimizer    0.13.9\r\n@angular-devkit/build-webpack      0.13.9\r\n@angular-devkit/core               7.3.9\r\n@angular-devkit/schematics         7.3.9\r\n@angular/cdk                       <error>\r\n@angular/cli                       7.3.9\r\n@angular/fire                      <error>\r\n@angular/flex-layout               <error>\r\n@angular/http                      <error>\r\n@angular/material                  <error>\r\n@angular/material-moment-adapter   <error>\r\n@angular/platform-server           <error>\r\n@ngtools/webpack                   7.3.9\r\n@schematics/angular                7.3.9\r\n@schematics/update                 0.13.9\r\nrxjs                               6.3.3\r\ntypescript                         3.2.4\r\nwebpack                            4.29.0\r\n\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n**Anything else relevant?** \r\nI have observed that when we configure lazy-loaded modules using `loadChildren` and the directly string pointing to the module that we want to lazy load. internally in the router-config \r\nas below code: \r\n<pre><code>\r\n this.router.config.unshift( {path:'base',loadChildren:'./modules/base/base.module#BaseModule'} );\r\n</code></pre>\r\nthen at runtime :this is replaced by a \"function\"-related to the Module (probably a NgFactory implementation of the module)\r\n<pre><code>this.router.config is:\r\n 0:\r\nloadChildren: ∆í ()\r\npath: \"base\"\r\n_loadedConfig: LoadedRouterConfig {routes: Array(1), module: NgModuleRef_}\r\n__proto__: Object\r\nlength: 1\r\n__proto__: Array(0) </code></pre>\r\n and that is returned in reference to the final router config which is being set. \r\n\r\nHowever when we try to load it dynamically, that is when the string defining my module that is to be dynamically loaded is being passed as a variable and the Route is built using it, when we use this route in the final routing config as below code: \r\n\r\n<pre><code>\r\nlet theOletObj: Route;\r\nlet  str='./modules/base/base.module#BaseModule';\r\n    this.theOletObj={path:'base',loadChildren:str};\r\n\r\n     this.router.config.unshift( this.theOletObj );\r\n</code>\r\n</pre>\r\n it leaves the value of \"loadChildren\" as a \"string \" \r\n<pre><code>0: {path: \"base\", loadChildren: \"./modules/base/base.module#BaseModule\"}\r\nlength: 1\r\n__proto__: Array(0)</code></pre>\r\n\r\n\r\nand dosent replace it with a \"function\"\r\n"
