    "body": "\r\n\r\n\r\n# üêû bug report\r\n\r\n### Affected Package\r\n<!-- Can you pin-point one or more @angular/* packages as the source of the bug? -->\r\n<!-- ‚úçÔ∏èedit: --> Unsure. I attempted to reproduce using ExtractTextPlugin, OptimizeCssAssetsPlugin, css-loader and cssnano but was unable to reproduce the behavior outside of an Angular project.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Is this a regression?\r\n\r\n<!-- Did this behavior use to work in the previous version? -->\r\n<!-- ‚úçÔ∏è--> No.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n<!-- ‚úçÔ∏è-->\r\nIn certain situations, multiple media queries for different classes are being combined into one which can change the order of css, breaking css-variable behavior.\r\n\r\nHere is the pattern:\r\n\r\n~~~~\r\n/* First media query for an unrelated class at a certain width */\r\n@media (min-width: 48em) {\r\n  .unrelated-class-share-media-query-1 {\r\n      font-size: 5px;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n}\r\n\r\n/* It only happens in my build when there is some other css in between the first media query and the variable definition */\r\n.filler-class-1 {\r\n  font-size: 15px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n/* Class that defines variable */\r\n.variable-definition {\r\n    --num-columns: 1;\r\n    --col-width: calc(100%/var(--num-columns));\r\n\r\n}\r\n\r\n.class-that-uses-variable {\r\n    flex-basis: var(--col-width);\r\n}\r\n\r\n/* Second media query of same width that changes the variable*/\r\n@media (min-width: 48em) {\r\n    .variable-definition {\r\n        --num-columns: 3;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n~~~~\r\n\r\nThis outputs:\r\n\r\n~~~~\r\n@media (min-width:48em) {\r\n\t.unrelated-class-share-media-query-1[_ngcontent-uni-c0] {\r\n\t\tfont-size: 5px\r\n\t}\r\n\t.variable-definition[_ngcontent-uni-c0] {\r\n\t\t--num-columns: 3\r\n\t}\r\n}\r\n\r\n.filler-class-1[_ngcontent-uni-c0] {\r\n\tfont-size: 15px\r\n}\r\n\r\n.variable-definition[_ngcontent-uni-c0] {\r\n\t--num-columns: 1;\r\n\t--col-width: calc(100%/var(--num-columns))\r\n}\r\n\r\n.class-that-uses-variable[_ngcontent-uni-c0] {\r\n\tflex-basis: var(--col-width)\r\n}\r\n\r\n~~~~\r\n\r\nThis causes the value of `--num-columns` to be 1 when it should be 3, because of the reordering.\r\n\r\n\r\n## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction\r\n<!--\r\nPlease create and share minimal reproduction of the issue starting with this template: https://stackblitz.com/fork/angular-issue-repro2\r\n-->\r\n<!-- ‚úçÔ∏è-->\r\nhttps://stackblitz.com/edit/angular-issue-repro2-jnyhvs?file=src%2Fapp%2Fapp.component.ts\r\n\r\n\r\n## üåç  Your Environment\r\n\r\n**Angular Version:**\r\n<pre><code>\r\n7.2.15\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n"
