    "body": "<!--üîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖ\r\n\r\nOh hi there! üòÑ\r\n\r\nTo expedite issue processing please search open and closed issues before submitting a new one.\r\nExisting issues often contain information about workarounds, resolution, or progress updates.\r\n\r\nüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖüîÖ-->\r\n\r\n# üìö Docs or angular.io bug report\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nIn the quickstart page, the CLI installation command installs version 7 instead of the release candidate that matches the docs\r\n\r\n## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nnpm install -g @angular/cli \r\nng --version\r\n\r\nAngular CLI: 7.3.9\r\nNode: 10.15.3\r\nOS: darwin x64\r\nAngular:\r\n```\r\n### What's the affected URL?**\r\n\r\nhttps://next.angular.io/guide/quickstart  \r\n\r\n### Suggested change\r\n\r\nTo install the release candidate the command should be \r\n\r\n```bash\r\nnpm install -g @angular/cli@next\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n"
