    "body": "Ivy uses object literals for speed and size. These are very hard to debugging because all types are an array or object literals without any useful hints to the developer. Similarly when profiling memory consumption it is hard to tell which object is which and so it is hard to track down memory pressure. This change enables constructor names for the Ivy dat structures making the code base more approachable.  \r\n\r\nHere is an example what the data structure look like now in debugger:\r\n![Screen Shot 2019-05-17 at 9 46 19 AM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/111951/57943710-94929d80-7889-11e9-9a32-1dd9bcf4248e.png)\r\n"
